The paper deals with market models and utility functions, which are topics typically studied in game theory (cs.GT), algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and economics and computation (cs.EC). The focus on equilibrium prices and welfare theorems further supports these categories.
